Notes for Installing Git

1. Download a Git installer from http://git-scm.com/downloads

2. Configure username and email address
	- not used as credentials on any of the git hosting sites
	- just used to keep record of the work that you do in the version control system

	$ git config --global user.name "myusername"

	$ git config --global user.email "myemail@email.com"

3. Create your first Git repository
	- use an init statement to create a repository

	$ git init project1

	$ cd project 1

	create file1.txt

	$ git add file1.txt

	$ git commit -m "My first commit"


4. Be sure to use '$ git init' to create folder where version control will take place


